<p><b>Ham</b> (<a href="/wiki/Hebrew_language" title="Hebrew language">Hebrew</a>: <span style="white-space:nowrap;font-size:125%" lang="he" dir="rtl" xml:lang="he">חָם</span>, <small><a href="/wiki/Modern_Israeli_Hebrew" title="Modern Israeli Hebrew" class="mw-redirect">Modern</a></small>&#160;<i><span title="he transliteration" class="Unicode" style="white-space:normal; text-decoration: none">H̱am</span></i>, <small><a href="/wiki/Tiberian_vocalization" title="Tiberian vocalization">Tiberian</a></small>&#160;<i><span title="Hebrew transliteration" class="Unicode" style="white-space:normal; text-decoration: none">Ḥām</span></i>; <a href="/wiki/Greek_language" title="Greek language">Greek</a> Χαμ, <i>Kham</i>; <a href="/wiki/Arabic" title="Arabic" class="mw-redirect">Arabic</a>: <span lang="ar" xml:lang="ar">حام</span>, <i>Ḥām</i>, "hot" or "burnt"), according to the <a href="/wiki/Table_of_Nations" title="Table of Nations" class="mw-redirect">Table of Nations</a> in the <i><a href="/wiki/Book_of_Genesis" title="Book of Genesis">Book of Genesis</a></i>, was a son of <a href="/wiki/Noah" title="Noah">Noah</a> and the father of <a href="/wiki/Cush_(Bible)" title="Cush (Bible)">Cush</a>, <a href="/wiki/Mizraim" title="Mizraim">Mizraim</a>, <a href="/wiki/Phut" title="Phut">Phut</a> and <a href="/wiki/Canaan_(son_of_Ham)" title="Canaan (son of Ham)">Canaan</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-2"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-3"><span>[</span>3<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p></p>
